The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 Patna, May 25: Twelve passengers of the Dibrugarh-bound Rajdhani Express were injured when 14 of the trains coaches derailed about 300km from Patna early this morning.           
	The railway administration and the police gave two different reasons for the accident.          
	While the railway authorities suspected Maoist-sponsored sabotage involving the damage on the two-metre stretch of the tracks as the reason, the police attributed the mishap to the poor maintenance of tracks, aggravated by heavy rainfall overnight.           
	The chief public relations officer of East-Central Railway said the derailment took place near Amba village between Kharik and Naugachhia stations under the zones Sonepur division at 6.30am. The driver applied emergency brakes after hearing the sound of an explosion on the tracks.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): Pakistan is set to bring up with India the issue of two hydel power units being constructed in Jammu and Kashmir when Indus Water Commissioners of the two countries meet here on May 31. Pakistan alleges that these projects violate the 1960 Indus Water Treaty that governs the two countries rights over six common rivers.                  
	 Melbourne (PTI): Indian American doctor Jayant Patel, accused of manslaughter in Australia, was not directly responsible for the death of a patient at the Bundaberg Base hospital, a surgeon has testified in court. Glyn Jamieson was being cross-examined by Patels counsel.                  
	 Rajkot (PTI): Three women and a 10-year-old girl were killed and 30 others injured when a matador carrying members of a marriage party collided with a truck in Surendranagar district, police said. A complaint has been registered and further investigations are on, police said.                  
	 Ahmedabad (PTI): A man has been arrested for allegedly raping a 24-year-old girl after abducting her and forcibly confining her in a flat for over one month, police said.
                                                                                                                                              
